  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen using the command `truffle init`, the default `truffle-config.js` file is mentioning the deprecated \"truffle-hdwallet-provider\" package. It'd be good replace it by \"@truffle/hdwallet-provider\".\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nIn a new directory, run the command `truffle init`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\n`truffle-config.js` to mention `@truffle/hdwallet-provider` as bellow:\r\n\r\n```\r\n/**\r\n...\r\n * To deploy via Infura you'll need a wallet provider (like @truffle/hdwallet-provider)\r\n...\r\n */\r\n\r\n// const HDWalletProvider = require('@truffle/hdwallet-provider');\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n```\r\n/**\r\n...\r\n * To deploy via Infura you'll need a wallet provider (like truffle-hdwallet-provider)\r\n...\r\n */\r\n\r\n// const HDWalletProvider = require('truffle-hdwallet-provider');\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: \r\n* Ethereum client:\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): v5.1.14\r\n* node version (`node --version`):\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): \r\n",
